In [38]:
def covaience(x,y):
    mean_x=sum(x)/float(len(x))
    mean_y=sum(y)/float(len(y))
    
    sub_x=[i-mean_x for i in x]
    sub_y=[i-mean_y for i in y]
    num=sum([sub_x[i]*sub_y[i] for i in range(len(sub_x))])
    dom=len(x)-1
    
    cov=num/dom
    return cov

x=df["a"]
y=df["b"]

covaience(x,y)
Out[38]:
6.35
